        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 27 at 12:41PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 1241 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 18
miles southeast of Moore, or 20 miles south of Lewistown, moving
north at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of southwestern Fergus
County.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
